<div id='tutoMOD_11' class='modal' style="display: none;">
  <div class='modalcontent_TUTO'>
    <h5>5. Export in tabular format </h5>
    <br>
    <p class='tutoTXT'>
      The download window allows you to define which variables to download for which reefs.
      <br><br>
      Use the list on the left to select the variables you want to download, then click on the <button style="width: 1cm; background-color: #0f497e;"><img src='public/buttons/buttonDA.svg' style="width: 100%;"></button> button to add them to the download list.
      <br><br>
      You will notice that the download list alread contains the custom variable that you created in the advanced mode. 
      <br><br>
      If you want to remove a variable from the download list, use the <button style="width: 1cm; background-color: #0f497e;"><img src='public/buttons/buttonDR.svg' style="width: 100%;"></button> button. 
      <br><br>
      By checking the box located just below the lists, you can decide whether to download the environmental variables only for the reefs that are located the closest to the Points of Interest.
      <br><br> 
      If you don't check this box, the environmnetal variables will be downloaded for all the reefs in the Area of Interest (i.e. all the reefs of the Red Sea).
      <br><br>
      To run the download, click on the <button style="background-color: #0f497e;">Download data</button> button. 
